# Troubleshooting

## Missing certificate

Error:

``` text
cannot load certificate ... fullchain.pem
```

Cause: Configured HTTPS before generating certificates.

Fix: Use HTTP-only configuration first.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Cloudflare 522

Check:

-   DNS points to EC2.
-   Port 80 open.
-   Nginx running.
-   Temporarily use DNS-only if proxying interferes with validation.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Timeout during connect

Usually caused by:

-   Security Group missing port 80.
-   UFW blocking port 80.
-   Nginx not listening on port 80.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Redirect loop / forced HTTPS

If Certbot fails while HTTP redirects immediately:

Remove:

``` nginx
return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
```

Generate certificate, then restore the redirect.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## HTTP/2 warning

Current Ubuntu package may show:

``` text
the "listen ... http2" directive is deprecated
```

but still accepts:

``` nginx
listen 443 ssl http2;
```

If:

``` nginx
listen 443 ssl;
http2;
```

fails with:

``` text
invalid number of arguments in "http2" directive
```

continue using the older syntax until your Nginx package fully supports
the standalone directive.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

